5. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The following elements constitute proprietary components of the
NOESIS DHCF-FNO system, including but not limited to:

• Deterministic Hybrid Control Framework (DHCF) architecture  
• Frozen Neural Operator (FNO) diffusion control methodology  
• CCCS cryptographic control chain system  
• IQS quality scoring framework and weight system  
• deterministic mastering pipeline architecture  
• LUFS drift contract system  
• Snapshot v16 reproducibility protocol  
• tamper-evident telemetry and audit trail system  
• Merkle-tree mastering verification structure  
• operator registry and checksum validation system  
• all associated mathematical formulas, theorems,
  engineering contracts and specifications.

All intellectual property rights remain exclusively with
Ilia Bolotnikov / AMAImedia.com.

This License does NOT transfer ownership, patents,
or intellectual property rights.

──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
6. GENERATOR AGNOSTICISM
──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

The NOESIS framework is designed to operate as a control layer
over frozen neural audio generation models.

Examples of compatible generative backends may include,
but are not limited to:

• MusicGen  
• Stable Audio  
• AudioLDM  
• Muse  
• other deterministic audio generation systems.

Compatibility with such systems does not affect the
intellectual property rights of the NOESIS framework.

